snippet.textDisplay: Pro tip if you wanna be super zesty you can make your own butter to go with your bread by getting some heavy whipping cream, I use the dairy free one, put it in your mixer, run that bad boy til the solids separate from liquids, then put the solids in a cheese cloth, gently squeeze out the liquids til the solid butter just starts to go through the cloth then viola you have a ball of homemade butter to put on your homemade bread. Also the liquids from it are fresh buttermilk so you can use that too.

Regarding it being kinda underdone in the middle, I bet if you make two short loaves (put two smaller dough blobs in, rather than one large one) next to each other in the pan, it’ll cook a little more evenly because it won’t be so thick in the middle.
I suspect that’s why a lot of bakery loaves look like that.
